New Features and Important Changes in GammaLib 00-06-01

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

September, 15th, 2012


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes module by module the most important
changes made since the last release of GammaLib.


2. Configuration
-----------------
The configuration script does no longer check for the presence of the
gammalib/__init__.py file. This file is generated upon installation
of the Python bindings, and is not shipped with the GammaLib library.
In version 00-06-00, a missing gammalib/__init__.py file was 
misinterpreted as a need for swig to build the Python bindings. On 
systems without swig the Pyhton bindings were thus not built.

The swig files are no longer installed in the GammaLib directory.
These files are indeed not needed.

The clang++ compiler takes now precedence over the g++ compiler. In
that way, clang++ will be selected by default on Mac OS X systems
(usually from Mac OS X 10.7 on).


